-- China Guodian May Invest 20 Billion Yuan in Solar, Wind Energy Projects
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-16T06:35:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-16/china-guodian-may-invest-20-billion-yuan-in-solar-wind-energy-projects.html
China Guodian Corp., the parent of
GD Power Development Co., plans to invest about 20 billion yuan
in the southern island province of Hainan in the five years
ending 2015.  China Guodian may build coal- and gas-fired power plants,
along with hydro, solar, wind and nuclear projects, the state-
run company said in a statement posted on its website today.  The electricity producer signed a power cooperation
agreement with the Hainan provincial government yesterday, it
said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Viljoen at 
 jviljoen@bloomberg.net  